I've been standing in front of the station for a while
Something doesn't feel right today
I couldn't get sleep last night, I'm tired
At this rate, I won't be able to smile at you
Hello?
Uh, I'm out of the house, I'm on my way
Just hang on, I'll be there soon
There's no traffic, huh? What will we do? Let's meet up first
Today is a special day, I¡¯ll tell you what
Today is the last day you and I will see each other
Out of the blue? No, I gave this a lot of thought
Kindling our love ended up kindling complaints
Midsummer night's sweet dream is over
There's no umbrella by your side now
You'll be alone, in the rain
I know you're kidding, I know you best

Stupid, you know, this is getting harder to handle
Stop joking around, you're making me nervous, stop
Just what's wrong with you?
This kind of attitude of yours makes me sick
I'm not joking, so please I want you to leave
I don't have the energy left in me to pull you back up
My body may be here with you, but my heart isn't
Yeah, I'm not usually like this, I don't even get mad
ut more time passes, I feel like I'm being choked
Being with you slowly began to feel like torture
It's like that everyday, so let's break up
Give it another thought, how can we break up?
No, it's over now, I acted like I still love you

comments.text:
personally I think this song is very under-appreciated and is not as 
popular as her other solo songs, and I understand that but it's amazingly 
wonderful to the ear. It has a very spring-ly feel and it's almost kind of 
a calming relaxing song, despite its sad lyrics. Many people have said that 
the rap doesn't fit, but I think it fits very well. His voice is a contrast 
to Raina's and it's nice to listen to. And this is my opinion, so I 
understand if you do not agree with it. Aside all that, this song is one of 
my all time favorites, and Raina has been doing well since her solo debut. 
Fighting!﻿

comments.text:
Blackjack here to support my adorable After School bias Raina! I was very 
happy when I found out that Raina would be making a solo debut because she 
deserves it so much. I always say that After School is the most underrated 
group in K-pop but I'd like to focus on Raina here, since it's her song. As 
expected, I love this. Raina's sweet singing voice and Kanto's rough rap 
are a perfect combination. I really like how the song is put in the form of 
a conversation between the man who is leaving and the girl who is so 
shocked and hurt that she turns to denial. The lyrics are beautiful and 
sorrowful with Raina's part being especially heartbreaking. The video is 
also nice, showing Raina going to meet her lover mixed with scenes of the 
couple's happy past memories. And as always, Raina looks lovely with her 
flawless skin and long legs. Raina hwaiting! <3﻿
